You basically need ruby, g++, and a POSIX operating  system  (GNU/Linux, or any UNIX).

You can build the assembler using the './configure;make' command.


== Compile the software with gcc on GNU/Linux ==

export CXXFLAGS="-O3 -Wall "
export LDFLAGS=$CXXFLAGS
./configure CXXFLAGS="$CXXFLAGS" LDFLAGS="$LDFLAGS" 
make




